The paper deals with abnormality detection in videos using spatio-temporal video parsing, which involves analyzing the foreground of a video to find normal spatio-temporal object hypotheses that can explain it. This involves techniques from computer vision (cs.CV) such as object detection and segmentation, as well as machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) for modeling the normal behavior of objects in videos. The paper also evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets (cs.MM) and uses graphical models for inference (cs.IR).
